  • Class
    Description
    ConversionException
    ConversionException is an exception that can occur when an object is converted to another object.
    StringConversionSupport
    StringConversionSupport is able to convert from strings to a number of primitive types and their corresponding wrapper types (Byte, Short, Integer, Long, Float, and Double), date and time types from the java.time package, and some additional common Java types such as File, BigDecimal, BigInteger, Currency, Locale, URI, URL, UUID, etc.
